COMMENTARY: Throughout Santa Fe’s history of cultural conflict, we’ve seen a lot of pain to go along with the beautiful diversity we have today.
We’ve seen Native people being oppressed and violently conquered.
We’ve seen Hispanic people marginalized and oppressed by a new Anglo-centric government.
A process by which the public may submit and comment upon events, memorials, monuments and markers that celebrate or recognize historic events or people for inclusion.
I believe we can be a leader in racial healing and transformation towards a more unified city, but it will take more than a mayor or city council.